&lt;font color=darkblue&gt;
&lt;img src=&quot;res/sk_blafp/common/rightarrow.gif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt; Description :&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; This is an example of using Oracle Text&#39;s MATCHES operator to classify the records into different categories. A set of queries that define our categories are saved in a table (TEXT_CLASSIFICATION). We then index the table to create a CTXRULE index which is used by MATCHES operator to classify the records.

[br/][br/]
&lt;font color=darkblue&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;res/sk_blafp/common/rightarrow.gif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt; Usage:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; Update classification criteria in the table beside. Once done, then click on the button &#39;Rebuild Classification Index&#39;. After allowing few seconds (~15 secs), refresh the report by selecting &#39;Refresh Report&#39; button.
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;</sawd:HTML>
